### Able Sailor
*Prerequisite: Human (Kul Tiras)*
<div style='margin-top:-5px;'></div>

You are completely at home aboard a ship, gaining the following benefits:
- Increase your Dexterity score by 1, to a maximum of 20.
- You gain proficiency in Acrobatics.
- When you make an Acrobatics check to keep your footing on a ship, a Sleight of Hand of hand skill check dealing with knots or ropes, or any check using Vehicles (Water), you double your proficiency bonus to the check.
- Climbing no longer costs you extra movement.

### [Arcane Manipulation]
*Prerequisite: Blood elf, nightborne*

### Arcane Teleportation
*Prerequisite: Blood elf, forsaken (elf), or nightborne*
<div style='margin-top:-5px;'></div>

Your study of highborne lore has unlocked arcane power that few other elves possess. Drawing on the ley lines, you can momentarily stride through space to shorten your path from one place to another. You gain the following benefits:
 - Increase your Intelligence or Charisma score by 1, to a maximum of 20.
 - You learn the *misty step* spell and can cast it once without expending a spell slot. You regain the ability to cast it in this way when you finish a short or long rest. Intelligence is your spellcasting ability for this spell.

### Bag of Tricks
*Prerequisite: Vulpera*
<div style='margin-top:-5px;'></div>

You carry around a small bag of trinkets and tools, which you can use to help get you out of trouble. As long as you have a bag or component pouch you can, as an action, reach into your it and bring forth an item to create one of the following effects. 
- *Damaging Vial:* You can make a ranged attack against a creature or object, dealing 1d6 acid or fire damage on a hit. If the target is a fiend or undead, you can instead deal radiant damage. This damage increases to 2d6 at 5th level, 3d6 at 11th level, and 4d6 at 17th level. 
- *Healing Vial:* You, or a creature you touch, regain <br/> 1d4 + 1 hit points. This increases to 2d4 + 2 at 5th level, 3d4 + 3 at 11th level, and 4d4 + 4 at 17th level.
- *Smoky Vial:* Choose a point within 20 feet. Smoke fills an area within a 5 foot radius of that point, lasting for 1 minute. A moderate wind disperses the smoke in 3 rounds, while a strong wind disperses it in 1 round. The radius of the smoke increases to 10 feet at 5th level, 15 feet at 11th level, and 20 feet at 17th level.

Any attack roll is made with proficiency and ranged attacks have a range of 20/60 feet. You can use this ability a number of times equal to your proficiency bonus and regain the ability to do so when you finish a long rest.

\columnbreak
### Better Chemistry
*Prerequisite: Goblin*
<div style='margin-top:-5px;'></div>

You've improved your living through chemistry, and have become an expert in its practices. You gain the following benefits:
 - Increase your Intelligence score by 1, to a max of 20.
 - You gain proficiency with alchemist's supplies. If you are already proficient with them, you double your profi-ciency bonus to checks you make with them.
 - As an action, you can identify one potion within 5 feet of you, as if you had tasted it.  You must see the liquid for this benefit to work.
 - Over the course of a short rest, you can temporarily improve the potency of one potion of healing of any rarity. You must have alchemist's supplies with you to improve the potions potency, and the potion must be within reach. For 1 hour after the short rest ends, a creature drinking the potion can forgo the potion's die roll and regains the maximum number of hit points that the potion can restore.

### Blood of Mannoroth
*Prerequisite: Orc*
<div style='margin-top:-5px;'></div>

Either through fel magic or through affinity with the nature of the Burning Legion, your latent corruption with the demonic blood flowing through your people has awakened. You gain the following benefits:
- Increase your Strength or Constitution score by 1, to a maximum of 20.
- You have resistance to your choice of fire or necrotic damage.
- You gain a bite attack as a natural weapon, which you can use to make unarmed strikes. If you hit with it, you deal piercing damage equal to 1d6 + your Strength modifier, instead of the bludgeoning damage normal for an unarmed strike.

### Brewer
*Prerequisite: Dwarf or pandaren*
<div style='margin-top:-5px;'></div>

[TBD.] You gain the following benefits:

- Increase your Constitution or Wisdom score by 1, to a maximum of 20.
- You gain proficiency in brewer's tools if you didn't already have it. You add double your proficiency bonus to checks you make with them.
- [TBD. Involves potions of healing, potentially some other brews.]

### Broken and Corrupted
*Prerequisite: Draenei (broken)*
<div style='margin-top:-5px;'></div>

[TBD. Idea is that the fel corruption is particularly strong, cutting you off from the Light and gaining physical bonuses.] You gain the following benefits:
- Increase your Strength, Dexterity, or Constitution score by 1, to a maximum of 20.
- You gain resistance to radiant damage.
- You count as one size larger when determining your carrying capacity and the weight you can push, drag, or lift.

\pagebreakNum
### Cannibalize
*Prerequisite: Forsaken*
<div style='margin-top:-5px;'></div>

[TBD.] You gain the following benefits:
- Increase your Constitution score by 1, to a maximum 20.
- You gain a bite attack as a natural weapon, which you can use to make unarmed strikes. If you hit with it, you deal piercing damage equal to 1d6 + your Strength modifier, instead of the bludgeoning damage normal for an unarmed strike.
- Using 1 minute, you can cannibalize the corpse of a humanoid or undead that has been dead for less than 1 day. When done, you regain a number of hit points equal to your level + your Constitution modifier. Once you use this trait, you can't use it again until you finish a short rest.

### Champion of the Light
*Prerequisite: Draenei (Lightforged)*
<div style='margin-top:-5px;'></div>

You learn to call on your inner connection to the Light, wielding it as a weapon against your foes. You gain the following benefits:
- Increase your Constitution or Charisma score by 1, to a maximum of 20.
- When you roll radiant damage for a spell you cast, you can reroll any roll of 1 on the radiant damage dice, but you must use the new roll, even if it is another 1.
- Whenever you cast a spell that deals radiant damage, you can cause light to shine forth from you until the end of your next turn. The light doesn’t harm you or your possessions, shedding bright light out to 30 feet and dim light for an additional 30 feet. While the light is present, any creature within 5 feet of you that hits you with a melee attack takes 1d4 radiant damage.

### Critter Friend
*Prerequisite: Night elf*
<div style='margin-top:-5px;'></div>

Your friendship with animals mystically deepens. You gain the following benefits:
 - You gain proficiency in the Animal Handling skill. If you're already proficient in it, your proficiency bonus is doubled for any check you make with it.
 - You learn the *speak with animals* spell and can cast it at will, without expending a spell slot. You also learn the *animal friendship* spell, and can cast it once with this feat, without expending a spell slot. You regain the ability to cast it in this way when you finish a long rest. Wisdom is your spellcasting ability for these spells.

\columnbreak
### Darnassian Heritage
*Prerequisite: Night elf*
<div style='margin-top:-5px;'></div>

Your connection to your kin deepens, unlocking unique gifts. You gain the following benefits:
 - Increase your Intelligence or Wisdom score by 1, to a maximum of 20.
 - You have advantage on Dexterity (Stealth) checks made in dim or unlit areas.
 - When you fail a death saving throw, you may call upon a wisp to change the dice to a success. The essence of the wisp continues to linger in your body for your next two long rests, making you unable to call for anothers aid.

### Diplomat
*Prerequisite: Human (Stormwind)*
<div style='margin-top:-5px;'></div>

You master the arts of diplomacy, gaining the following benefits:
- Increase your Charisma score by 1, to a maximum of 20.
- You gain proficiency in the Persuasion skill. If you are already proficient in this skill, you add double your proficiency bonus to checks you make with it.
- If you spend 1 minute talking to someone who can understand what you say, you can make a Charisma (Persuasion) check contested by the creature’s Wisdom (Insight) check. If you or your companions are fighting the creature, your check automatically fails. If your check succeeds, the target is charmed by you as long as it remains within 60 feet of you and for 1 minute thereafter.

### Distance Runner
*Prerequisite: Tauren or worgen*
<div style='margin-top:-5px;'></div>

[TBD. Covers Running Wild and Plainsrunning.] You gain the following benefits:
- Increase your Constitution score by 1, to a maximum of 20.
- You have advantage on saving throws to avoid exhaustion levels from a forced march.
- When determining travel pace, double your movement speed. If you have no more than one level of exhaustion, you can also maintain a travel pace of up to four times your speed for up to one hour, but then you gain two levels of exhaustion. It takes at least 1 minute to get up to speed, and you only gain these benefits as long as you are unmounted.

### Dwarven Fortitude
*Prerequisite: Dwarf*
<div style='margin-top:-5px;'></div>

You have the blood of dwarf heroes flowing through your veins. You gain the following benefits:
 - Increase your Constitution score by 1, to a max of 20.
 - Whenever you take the Dodge action in combat, you can spend one Hit Die to heal yourself. Roll the die, add your Constitution modifier, and regain a number of hit points equal to the total (minimum of 1).

### Dwarven Sharpshooter 
*Prerequisite: Dwarf (ironforge)*
<div style='margin-top:-5px;'></div>

[Benefits when wielding firearms.]

\pagebreakNum
### Elusiveness
*Prerequisite: Night elf*
<div style='margin-top:-5px;'></div>

You are able to use your ability to meld into the shadows to escape from harm. You gain the following benefits:
- Increase your Dexterity or Wisdom by 1, to a maximum of 20.
- You have advantage on Dexterity (Stealth) checks.
- Immediately after you take damage, you can use a reaction to magically become invisible until the end of your next turn or until you attack, deal damage, or force someone to make a saving throw. Once you use this ability, you can't do so again until you finish a short or long rest.

### Elven Accuracy
*Prerequisite: Blood elf, forsaken (elf), night elf, nightborne, or void elf*
<div style='margin-top:-5px;'></div>

The accuracy of elves is legendary, especially that of elf archers and spellcasters. You have an uncanny aim with attackss that rely on precision rather than brute force. You gain the following benefits:
 - Increase your Dexterity, intelligence, Wisdom, or Charisma score by 1, to a maximum of 20.
 - Whenever you have advantage on an attack roll using Dexterity, Intelligence, Wisdom, or Charisma, you can reroll one of the dice once.

### Embrace of the Void
*Prerequisite: Void elf*
<div style='margin-top:-5px;'></div>

You have strengthened your ability to call upon the void infused in your body. You gain the following benefits:
 - Increase your Intelligence, Wisdom, or Charisma score by 1, to a maximum of 20.
 - When you roll necrotic damage for a spell you cast, you can reroll any roll of 1 on the necrotic damage dice, but you must use the new roll, even if it is another 1.
 - When you cast a spell that deals necrotic damage, you can cause void to wreathe you until the end of your next turn. The void doesn't harm, and reduces all light within 30 feet to darkness, and light within an additional 30 feet to dim light. While the void is present, any creature within 5 feet of you that hits you with a melee attack takes 1d4 damage.
 
### Eredar Heritage
*Prerequisite: Draenei*
<div style='margin-top:-5px;'></div>

The eredar people are known throughout the Great Dark Beyond to be supremely talented magic users, something that you embody as an example. Choose a class: druid, mage, priest, shaman, or warlock. You learn one cantrip, one 1st level spell, and one 2nd level spell based on the class you chose, as seen in the Eredar Heritage table. 

You can cast your 1st and 2nd level spell each once per day without expending a spell slot and regain the ability to do so when you finish a long rest. Your spellcasting ability for these spells depends on the class you chose: Charisma for priest; Wisdom for druid or shaman; or Intelligence for mage or warlock.

\columnbreak
##### Eredar Heritage
Class   | Cantrip           | 1st Level <br/> Spell   | 2nd Level Spell
--------|-------------------|-------------------|----------------
