### Faction Grudge
*Prerequisite: Any race*
<div style='margin-top:-5px;'></div>

You have a deep hatred for a particular member of the opposite faction. Choose two races of the opposite faction to bear the burden of your wrath (each race includes all of it's sub races). You gain the following benefits:
 - Increase your Strength, Constitution, or Wisdom by 1, to a maximum of 20.
 - During the first round of combat against your chosen foes, your attack rolls against them have advantage.
 - When any of your chosen foes make an opportunity attack against you, it makes the attack roll with disadvantage.
 - When you make an Intelligence (Arcana, History, Nature, or Religion) check to recall information about your chosen foes, you add double your proficiency bonus to the check, even if you're not normally proficient in the skill.

### Feed the Addiction
*Prerequisite: Blood Elf*
<div style='margin-top:-5px;'></div>

[Can gain temp hp when you save against spells.]

\pagebreakNum
### Hardened Predator
*Prerequisite: Worgen*
<div style='margin-top:-5px;'></div>

You have grown accustom to your worgen form, realizing the benefits that come with it. You gain the following benefits while in your worgen form:
 - You have advantage on Wisdom (Perception) checks that rely on smell.
 - While both your hands are empty, you can take the Dash action as a bonus action, running on all fours.
 - Your claws grow large, and become natural weapons, which you can use to make unarmed strikes. If you hit with them, you deal slashing damage equal to 1d4 + your Strength modifier, instead of normal bludgeoning damage for an unarmed strike.
 - If you make a bite attack as an action, you can use your bonus action to make an attack with your claws.

#### Hardened Predator
*Prerequisite: Worgen*

You have grown accustom to your worgen form, realizing the benefits that come with it. You gain the following benefits while in your worgen form:
- Your movement speed increases by 10 feet.
- Your claws grow large, and become natural weapons, which you can use to make unarmed strikes. If you hit with them, you deal slashing damage equal to 1d4 + your Strength modifier, instead of normal bludgeoning damage for an unarmed strike.
- If you make a bite attack as an action, you can use your bonus action to make an attack with your claws.
- While both your hands are empty, you can run on all fours, doubling your speed until the end of the tum. Once you use this trait, you can't use it again until you move 0 feet on one of your turns.

### Human Endurance
*Prerequisite: Human*
<div style='margin-top:-5px;'></div>

Your enduring spirit allows you to better avoid deadly blows. You gain the following benefits:
- Increase your Dexterity, Constitution, or Charisma score by 1, to a maximum of 20.
- When a creature you can see hits you with an attack roll, you can use your reaction to force that creature to reroll. Once you use this ability, you can’t use it again until you roll initiative at the start of combat or until you finish a short or long rest.


### Inspirational Spirit
*Prerequisite: Human*
<div style='margin-top:-5px;'></div>

Your spirit to defy the odds can inspire your allies, preventing them from faltering at the worst times.

When an ally you can see within 30 feet of you rolls a 1 on the d20 for an attack roll, an ability check, or a saving throw, you can use your reaction to let the ally reroll the die. The ally must use the new roll.

When you use this ability, you can't use your Human Spirit racial trait before the end of your next turn

### Keen Nose
*Prerequisite: Worgen*
<div style='margin-top:-5px;'></div>

Your nose is especially keen, able to sniff out hidden enemies. You gain the following benefits:
- You have advantage on Wisdom (Perception) checks based on smell.
- You can detect the presence, but not exact location, of other creatures within 30 feet by sense of smell. Being downwind of the source doubles this range while being upwind halves it. Strong scents like smoke or rotting garbage can be detected at twice the range while overpowering scents such as skunk musk can be detected at triple the range. If you are within 5 feet of the scent's source, you pinpoint its location.
- You can make a Wisdom (Survival) check to find or follow a scent. The typical DC for a fresh trail is 10 (or 20, if obscured by false and/or powerful odors), increasing or decreasing depending on how strong the quarry’s odor is, the number of creatures, and the age of the trail. For each hour that the trail is cold, the DC increases by 2. The type of surface, surface conditions, and poor visibility does not affect the DC.

### Like A Boss
*Prerequisite: Goblin*
<div style='margin-top:-5px;'></div>

You are accustomed to using others to avoid being attacked. You gain the following benefits:
- Increase your Dexterity or Charisma score by 1, to a maximum of 20.
- When a creature you can see targets you with an attack and another creature is within 5 feet of you, you can use your reaction to impose disadvantage on the attack roll. Once you use this ability, you can’t do so again until you finish a short or long rest.
- [TBD.]

### Mana Tap
*Prerequisite: Blood elf*
<div style='margin-top:-5px;'></div>

Following the teachings of Prince Kael'thas, you are better able to absorb and release magical energy. You gain the following benefits:
- You learn the *arcane blast* cantrip. Intelligence is your spellcasting ability for this spell. 
- You can also unleash the cantrip as an Arcane Torrent, increasing the damage dice from 1d8 to 1d12. You can do so a number of times equal to your proficiency bonus and regain the ability to do so when you finish a short or long rest.
- When you successfully save against a spell or spell-like effect, you can gain one of the following benefits: you regain a use of Spell Turning, you can regain a casting of *detect magic* from Arcane Knowledge, or you regain all expended uses of Arcane Torrent. You do not gain this benefit if you have used Spell Turning this turn.

### Masquerade
*Prerequisite: Nightborne*
<div style='margin-top:-5px;'></div>

The masquerade, the dance of disguise and detection, is an important part of Nightborne culture. You are better than most at performing this charade, gaining the following benefits:
- Increase your Intelligence, Wisdom, or Charisma by 1, to a maximum of 20.
- You learn the *disguise self* spell and can cast it without expending a spell slot. You regain the ability to do so when you finish a short or long rest. 
- You have an advantage on Charisma (Deception) and Charisma (Performance) checks when trying to pass yourself off as a different person.
- You have advantage on Intelligence (Investigation) checks made to disbelieve illusions and can do so as a bonus action.

